{
  "answer": "**The second couplet (sher, marked as paragraph [p-c69a90]) of chapter 23 in *Diwan-E-Zauq* (\"Jo kuch ke hai duniya mein woh insaan ke liye hai\") is:**\n\n> Your pagan hair—what business has it with my soul?  \n> My heart's a shrine reserved for faith's devoted light.[^1]\n\nThis is from the English translation variant.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Sheikh Ibrahim Zauq, *Diwan-E-Zauq*, ch. 23 (\"Jo kuch ke hai duniya mein woh insaan ke liye hai\"), [paragraph](/works/sheikh-ibrahim-zauq-diwan-e-zauq-0fa798/23-jo-kuch-ke-hai-duniya-mein-woh-insaan-ke-liye-hai/translation/#p-c69a90).\n\n[^2]: The chapter consists of 11 couplets in verse layout; this is the second, following the matla (opening couplet) [p-b05a2c].[^3]\n\n[^3]: Sheikh Ibrahim Zauq, *Diwan-E-Zauq*, ch. 23, [full chapter](/works/sheikh-ibrahim-zauq-diwan-e-zauq-0fa798/23-jo-kuch-ke-hai-duniya-mein-woh-insaan-ke-liye-hai/translation/).",
